{
  "text": "• and 35 •3 . The computed angles for each γ j of this implementation are presented in Table I . The second path considered is one determined by an immediate predecessor of the ZZTOPP algorithm, [CITATION_1] which gives a lower cost than the reference path, as shown in Table I . This computed path was executed with the pitch angles computed by use of the sampling resolution optimization algorithm given in Section V. The computed angles for each γ j of this path are also presented in Table I . The experimental results are divided into three parts to test separate portions of the algorithms. First, we will compare collected science data in a region of high interest for the minimum, standard and maximum dive and ascent angles, 15",
